1
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:00,530
[Complete Registry Information]

2
00:01:00,530 --> 00:01:03,710
We looked into Jeongjik Nursing
Home as you asked.

3
00:01:03,710 --> 00:01:06,450
It's owned by Baekho Foundation.

4
00:01:06,450 --> 00:01:08,740
Recently, it was passed down

5
00:01:08,740 --> 00:01:10,900
to their only daughter, Baek Hye Mi.

6
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:12,200
[CEO: Baek Hye Mi since May 17, 2022]

7
00:01:22,170 --> 00:01:24,670
[Geum Ju]

8
00:01:24,670 --> 00:01:27,860
[Jeongjik Nursing Home]

9
00:01:33,550 --> 00:01:35,310
Hey...

10
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:36,490
You stay here.

11
00:01:36,490 --> 00:01:37,980
No, let's go together.

12
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:41,870
No, you did enough by coming here with me.

13
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:43,310
From here, I'll go alone.

14
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:44,600
No way.

15
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:47,600
- What if something happens to-
- Please, Geum Ju.

16
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:51,110
I need to take care of this myself.

17
00:01:54,050 --> 00:01:55,790
I'll call you.

18
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:16,110
Die, you bastard!

19
00:02:16,110 --> 00:02:17,580
Die!

20
00:02:20,670 --> 00:02:22,400
Ms. Baek...

21
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,640
Ms. Baek!

22
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:49,730
Please wake up!

23
00:02:49,730 --> 00:02:51,590
Please!

24
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:55,960
[Surgery Center]

25
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:01,400
Are you okay?

26
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:11,640
Why must you go this far?

27
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:13,170
Killing you...

28
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:17,240
is the greatest revenge I can take on her.

29
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,370
Mr. Seo Ui Jun.

30
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:52,160
[Jeongjik Nursing Home]

31
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:58,230
Your friend witnessed your father

32
00:03:58,230 --> 00:04:00,880
chasing after you while sitting
in the car and called us.

33
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:03,360
We're scanning the nearby area.

34
00:04:06,790 --> 00:04:08,430
Ui Jun.

35
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,940
Thankfully, the surgery went well.

36
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,310
- She'll move to a hospital room.
- Really?

37
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,620
Detective.

38
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:17,430
Could we talk later?

39
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:19,380
Yes, let's do that.

40
00:04:20,410 --> 00:04:21,300
Hurry, go.

41
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,340
I'll go to the Ms. Baek's house and get her things.

42
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:24,740
Okay.

43
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:47,150
[Celebrating getting his residency]

44
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:48,910
[31st birthday]

45
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:50,570
[A new beginning]

46
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:20,660
To my son, Ui Jun, who may one day read this...

47
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,040
Your grandfather

48
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:29,350
never accepted your dad.

49
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:32,020
Your dad was just a poor college student

50
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:34,120
receiving foundation's aid.

51
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,540
Abort the child immediately

52
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:38,580
and leave this country.

53
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:41,680
Don't touch this baby.

54
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,330
Please.

55
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,600
Or else I'll die.

56
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:54,860
I had no choice but to leave you behind.

57
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:01,270
I came back to Korea

58
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:04,030
and found you, whom I dreamed of,

59
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,650
but I just couldn't approach you.

60
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:10,130
Because at the end of the day,

61
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:13,520
I had abandoned you.

62
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:17,090
I figured it'd hurt less

63
00:06:17,090 --> 00:06:20,000
if you thought I was dead.

64
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,320
Happy birthday.

65
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,200
Thank you.

66
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:34,100
Whoa!

67
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:37,000
I was actually meaning to buy a scarf.

68
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:40,420
If only I could be by your side,

69
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:44,190
I thought you never had to find out who I really am.

70
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:45,350
It's such a nice color.

71
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:46,800
Looks good.

72
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,700
Doctor.

73
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,910
Yes? Just a moment.

74
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,410
- He hasn't been discharged yet?
- No.

75
00:06:54,410 --> 00:06:56,240
We'll take care of it this afternoon.

76
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,160
I've already submitted the paperwork.

77
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:01,900
[Father]
I'm in Seoul.

78
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,180
Let's meet.

79
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:05,430
I'll come to the hospital.

80
00:07:11,210 --> 00:07:15,180
No, I'll come to you, Father.

81
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:19,710
Nurse Jeong, you're off this afternoon, right?

82
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:20,780
Yes.

83
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:22,760
I'm sorry, but could you cover my shift?

84
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,460
Something urgent came up.

85
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:25,630
Sure.

86
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:26,930
Thank you.

87
00:07:26,930 --> 00:07:31,760
But that incident happened that day.

88
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,980
It's all my fault.

89
00:07:40,690 --> 00:07:42,920
Nurse Jeong,

90
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,850
and throwing you into that hell, too.

91
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,840
So, I promised myself.

92
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:54,490
I'll make him pay for his crimes.

93
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:58,820
I'll make sure he stays locked up
until the day he dies.

94
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:03,060
My beloved son...

95
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,210
I will...

96
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:08,180
protect you.

97
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:24,960
Doctor...

98
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:27,900
Are you okay?

99
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,580
Are you hurt?

100
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:58,390
You should have told me.

101
00:08:59,990 --> 00:09:03,000
You should've told me everything.

102
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,810
I was scared...

103
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:14,200
that you'd say you never wanted to see me again...

104
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,050
But still...

105
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:19,880
I can't believe you hid everything...

106
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:22,940
I'm sorry.

107
00:09:24,170 --> 00:09:26,690
It's all my fault.

108
00:09:30,420 --> 00:09:32,740
It's all because of me...

109
00:10:16,740 --> 00:10:20,500
I don't know how to process all this.

110
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:25,810
Of course, you don't.

111
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:32,860
It's always been an empty space.

112
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:35,170
To me, Mom...

113
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:38,840
didn't exist in this world.

114
00:10:41,310 --> 00:10:45,400
I'm sure it was tough
for Ms. Baek to keep it a secret.

115
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:49,430
She probably blamed herself
for your loneliness and pain.

116
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:54,550
That's why she fiercely protected
you from your father.

117
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:58,270
I know.

118
00:10:59,430 --> 00:11:01,520
I know all that.

119
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:05,850
But I don't know how
to explain how I feel right now.

120
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:09,090
I don't know how to face her.

121
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:14,620
If a patient came to me

122
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:17,890
and told me all this,

123
00:11:17,890 --> 00:11:20,550
what would I say to them?

124
00:11:25,650 --> 00:11:28,230
I don't think I could find an answer.

125
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:34,330
I understand.

126
00:11:35,830 --> 00:11:37,700
That makes sense.

127
00:11:53,730 --> 00:11:55,730
I can't believe it.

128
00:11:55,730 --> 00:11:58,120
That Ms. Baek is Ui Jun's mom...

129
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,850
Right?

130
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:03,150
She left, trusting that he'd be raised well.

131
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:05,590
Seeing him be so lonely and in pain

132
00:12:05,590 --> 00:12:07,460
must've broken her heart.

133
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:11,470
That's probably why
she cared so deeply for Ui Jun.

134
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:12,560
Yeah.

135
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:14,800
Apparently, she paid for his college
tuition, living expenses,

136
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:18,000
and his study abroad program through scholarships

137
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:20,510
and grants without him knowing.

138
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:25,220
Gosh, yet she couldn't step forward as his mom.

139
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:28,360
Imagine how much she kept bottled up inside.

140
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:31,290
So, is Ms. Baek okay?

141
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:34,320
Yeah, fortunately, the surgery went well.

142
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,650
Thank goodness, seriously.

143
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:40,920
Actually, I was thinking we should
all visit the hospital together.

144
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:43,950
That's why I suggested we meet
at your place, Hyungnim.

145
00:12:43,950 --> 00:12:46,970
Let's go later.

146
00:12:46,970 --> 00:12:48,740
There are police stationed by the hospital room,

147
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:51,280
so I heard the mood is a bit chaotic.

148
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:55,630
And they said Ms. Baek needs to rest for a while.

149
00:12:56,470 --> 00:12:59,820
By the way, how's Ui Jun doing?

150
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,740
He must be in big shock.

151
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:02,860
Of course.

152
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:06,530
To find out that Ms. Baek, who's been
by your side, is your mom?

153
00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:08,320
Plus, he must be so nervous.

154
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:10,850
His father, the source of things bad,
still hasn't been found.

155
00:13:10,850 --> 00:13:12,460
Right?

156
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:14,210
Someone died because of his father,

157
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:17,070
which led to Ui Jun leaving
the university hospital.

158
00:13:17,070 --> 00:13:19,400
Alcohol is the enemy. Alcohol is the problem.

159
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,860
It's not just the alcohol.

160
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:24,320
It's the people who drink recklessly.

161
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,430
Anyway, I hope they find him soon.

162
00:13:28,430 --> 00:13:31,850
Only then can Ui Jun and Ms. Baek
finally have some peace.

163
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:33,550
I know.

164
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:38,600
No wonder Ms. Baek went through
all that to that extent.

165
00:13:39,350 --> 00:13:41,780
My goodness...

166
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:44,800
Kidnapping, confinement...

167
00:13:45,740 --> 00:13:48,140
I acknowledge all of it.

168
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:50,680
I'll cooperate fully with the investigation.

169
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:52,990
We'll contact you once we schedule

170
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:54,880
your questioning at the station.

171
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,630
How about that man?

172
00:13:58,990 --> 00:14:00,980
You still haven't found him?

173
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:03,060
No. Not yet.

174
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:05,780
Please keep protecting Dr. Seo.

175
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:08,550
You never know what he might try to do again.

176
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:11,320
We're keeping a close watch,

177
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,450
so please don't worry too much.

178
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,990
All right, then.

179
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:26,670
Are you okay? Should I call a nurse?

180
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,410
No, it's okay.

181
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:31,570
You didn't need to come.
I'm sure you're busy at work.

182
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:34,430
Don't say that. It's okay.

183
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:39,480
How's Dr. Seo's...

184
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:43,290
hand? Is it okay?

185
00:14:43,290 --> 00:14:46,580
Yes, fortunately, the wound wasn't deep.

186
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:49,650
But he looked tired, so I told him to rest.

187
00:14:49,650 --> 00:14:52,140
I said I'd stay by your side.

188
00:14:57,340 --> 00:14:59,960
He must be struggling.

189
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:02,770
I think...

190
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:06,470
he just needs some time.

191
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:18,800
You'll stay by Dr. Seo's side, right?

192
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,570
No matter what happens.

193
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:25,540
Pardon?

194
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:26,860
Please help him

195
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:29,890
hold on to the happiness he finally found.

196
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:33,320
I'm worried

197
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:36,740
that he'll push you away again.

198
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:41,310
What do you mean to push me away again?

199
00:15:41,310 --> 00:15:46,190
♫ Amongst strangers ♫

200
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:52,910
♫ Hiding my loneliness ♫

201
00:15:55,070 --> 00:15:59,910
♫ Under the pouring rain ♫

202
00:16:02,510 --> 00:16:05,650
♫ I hide my wet eyes ♫

203
00:16:05,650 --> 00:16:07,820
I'm worried

204
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:11,230
that he'll push you away again.

205
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:20,690
♫ I regret, lonely ♫

206
00:16:22,490 --> 00:16:29,850
♫ I can't turn back the time that is long gone ♫

207
00:16:29,850 --> 00:16:34,620
♫ Becomes the shade of life ♫

208
00:16:42,430 --> 00:16:44,260
I'm working late tonight.

209
00:16:44,260 --> 00:16:46,540
Make sure you eat, even if your heart feels heavy.

210
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:48,500
That's how you stay strong.

211
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:52,760
One thing's for sure. Only happiness awaits.

212
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:54,790
Let's be happy.

213
00:17:00,570 --> 00:17:02,700
Can I really?

214
00:17:13,110 --> 00:17:15,850
What if you end up in danger, too?

215
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:36,030
What's this, Seo Ui Jun? Not even replying...

216
00:17:42,230 --> 00:17:46,090
Where's a porridge place nearby...

217
00:18:03,610 --> 00:18:04,990
Hi, Mom.

218
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:07,680
I got some porridge for Ms. Baek.

219
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:10,080
She can't eat regular food for a while.

220
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:11,660
Okay.

221
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:52,620
- Ui Jun.
- Are you okay?

222
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,590
What's with you, man?

223
00:19:02,980 --> 00:19:05,790
Hey, Seon Uk. Hey, are you okay?

224
00:19:07,330 --> 00:19:09,270
[Seon Uk]
I'm leaving to get some air.

225
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:11,410
I asked Master Kim to look
after the taekwondo studio.

226
00:19:11,410 --> 00:19:12,990
Don't worry.

227
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:22,700
- Auntie.
- Yes, Hwa Yeong.

228
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,320
- You're here.
- You can stay lying down.

229
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:26,630
I'm okay.

230
00:19:26,630 --> 00:19:29,460
Hwa Yeong, want to go play with Auntie?

231
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:31,250
Yes, sounds good.

232
00:19:32,540 --> 00:19:34,740
Mom, feel better soon.

233
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:35,930
Okay.

234
00:19:35,930 --> 00:19:37,070
Let's go, Auntie.

235
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:39,370
Gosh, so cute. See you later.

236
00:19:39,370 --> 00:19:40,930
My baby.

237
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:43,840
I heard you're feeling weak and exhausted.

238
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:47,140
Your father-in-law personally brewed
this 6-year-old red ginseng.

239
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:49,080
He sent me to feed it to you.

240
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:52,330
You're so lucky to get treated like this.

241
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:55,670
No, I don't deserve this kind of treatment.

242
00:19:56,380 --> 00:19:58,810
Look at you, speaking the truth for once.

243
00:19:59,810 --> 00:20:01,530
Gosh, my legs...

244
00:20:03,050 --> 00:20:05,860
What's this? "I'm leaving to get some air"?

245
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,320
Goodness...

246
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,840
Mother...

247
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,270
Yes?

248
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:15,000
I think...

249
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,680
I'm being punished.

250
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:20,400
For driving a nail into your heart.

251
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:23,100
What are you saying now?

252
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:28,220
Seon Uk likes...

253
00:20:29,130 --> 00:20:30,740
Hyeon Ju.

254
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,120
He left home because I was against it.

255
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,580
What?

256
00:20:37,910 --> 00:20:41,770
I dated Yeong Woong against your wishes.

257
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:46,400
And now I'm paying for it. Every bit of it.

258
00:20:46,430 --> 00:20:47,780
That's enough.

259
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:50,050
You're not being punished.

260
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:57,200
Let me be honest.

261
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,300
I regretted it a lot.

262
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:07,750
Saying harsh things to you
and opposing your marriage.

263
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:09,140
What?

264
00:21:11,260 --> 00:21:14,400
Maybe it's because he met his soulmate.

265
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:19,900
When I see my son living his happiest life,

266
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:24,700
gosh, I realize I was stubborn for no reason.

267
00:21:26,210 --> 00:21:29,040
If I had accepted you from the start,

268
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:33,380
I thought we could've been closer, too.

269
00:21:34,870 --> 00:21:36,290
Mother...

270
00:21:36,970 --> 00:21:40,590
But still, I kept snapping whenever I saw you.

271
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:44,970
If I didn't, it felt like I was
admitting I was wrong.

272
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:47,280
It hurt my pride, too.

273
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,130
Seon Hwa.

274
00:21:52,950 --> 00:21:56,450
You can't stop it even if you stop them.

275
00:21:56,450 --> 00:22:00,240
You can't split them up even if you tried.

276
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:04,180
You know better than anyone. Right?

277
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:07,210
Cheer them on.

278
00:22:07,820 --> 00:22:10,730
Don't live to regret it like me.

279
00:22:14,450 --> 00:22:16,110
Mother...

280
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:18,430
Aigoo...

281
00:22:18,430 --> 00:22:22,170
Stop crying away all your strength.

282
00:22:22,170 --> 00:22:24,070
Aigoo...

283
00:22:24,930 --> 00:22:28,110
Where is that rascal,

284
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:31,590
after upsetting his sister this much?

285
00:22:31,590 --> 00:22:33,230
Aigoo...

286
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:41,990
Hey, slow down, slow down.

287
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,710
I told you, it's my first meal in two days.

288
00:22:45,710 --> 00:22:48,410
So, who told you to lose your bag
when you got to Seoul?

289
00:22:48,410 --> 00:22:49,450
No phone, no wallet...

290
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:51,150
How can you show up looking homeless?

291
00:22:51,150 --> 00:22:52,380
What do you mean?

292
00:22:52,380 --> 00:22:55,240
I made it here, and that's why
you're buying me food right now.

293
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,890
Geez.

294
00:23:01,790 --> 00:23:03,320
Yes, Detective.

295
00:23:03,970 --> 00:23:06,800
No, he hasn't shown up.

296
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:12,970
You're still tracking him, right?

297
00:23:15,210 --> 00:23:17,270
What's all that about?

298
00:23:19,210 --> 00:23:20,560
Yes.

299
00:23:21,250 --> 00:23:23,720
I'll come to the station tomorrow.

300
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:27,290
And...

301
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:31,390
how is the investigation into
Jeongjik Nursing Home going?

302
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:33,170
What?

303
00:23:33,170 --> 00:23:34,690
Really?

304
00:23:34,690 --> 00:23:36,350
Ms. Baek is his mom?

305
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,300
So, is Ms. Baek okay?

306
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:41,400
Yeah, thankfully.

307
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:44,780
And Ui Jun's dad is still missing?

308
00:23:44,780 --> 00:23:46,680
You think we'd be here if we knew?

309
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:48,060
Just shut up and eat.

310
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:51,080
I'm only telling you so you stop acting clueless.

311
00:23:52,130 --> 00:23:53,830
Fine.

312
00:23:53,830 --> 00:23:55,670
I'm not all that thoughtless, you know.

313
00:23:55,670 --> 00:23:57,860
Then, why did you run away
from home in your thirties?

314
00:23:57,860 --> 00:23:59,630
I told you I didn't run away.

315
00:23:59,630 --> 00:24:03,060
I told you I came to Seoul to clear my head.

316
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:06,230
I didn't think I could collect
my thoughts in Bochun.

317
00:24:06,230 --> 00:24:08,420
What do you mean collect your thoughts?

318
00:24:10,050 --> 00:24:12,170
Are you talking about my sister right now?

319
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:15,300
- You knew?
- I didn't want to know.

320
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:17,750
Seon Hwa and my sister's
30-year friendship was shattered.

321
00:24:17,750 --> 00:24:20,270
All because of you. What's this?

322
00:24:21,830 --> 00:24:23,100
Yeah.

323
00:24:24,030 --> 00:24:25,920
It's all my fault.

324
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:30,070
No matter how hard my sister pushed back,

325
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:32,420
I didn't think she could break my will.

326
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:36,030
I swore I'd never give up on Hyeon Ju,
even if it killed me.

327
00:24:36,030 --> 00:24:38,180
I swore I'd dedicate

328
00:24:38,180 --> 00:24:41,360
the rest of my life to make Hyeon Ju happy.

329
00:24:42,850 --> 00:24:44,790
But that resolve...

330
00:24:46,030 --> 00:24:47,950
My stubbornness...

331
00:24:49,570 --> 00:24:51,950
didn't bring her happiness.

332
00:24:53,930 --> 00:24:57,210
I didn't know it'd cause her pain
she can never heal from.

333
00:25:01,620 --> 00:25:04,860
So, I decided to let go of my feelings.

334
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,440
But Geum Ju...

335
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:17,410
I'm not confident.

336
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,950
It's too hard.

337
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:26,810
I might die of a broken heart.

338
00:25:40,180 --> 00:25:42,040
I'm sorry.

339
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:45,110
You must be dealing with a lot with Ui Jun.

340
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:59,810
You should've called if you
were coming to my office.

341
00:26:01,410 --> 00:26:05,110
Yeah, that didn't even cross my mind.

342
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:08,360
All I thought about was seeing
you as soon as possible.

343
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,030
Why?

344
00:26:10,030 --> 00:26:11,940
I was worried.

345
00:26:13,170 --> 00:26:15,110
I was worried about you.

346
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:20,980
I was more worried.

347
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:24,340
That you might cut me off again.

348
00:26:25,820 --> 00:26:27,850
I'm worried

349
00:26:27,850 --> 00:26:30,980
that he'll push you away again.

350
00:26:31,710 --> 00:26:34,200
What do you mean to push me away again?

351
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:37,540
I heard it was because of him that time, too.

352
00:26:38,550 --> 00:26:42,320
Because he was scared that he'd hurt you.

353
00:26:45,290 --> 00:26:46,120
[I love you, Han Geum Ju]

354
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:48,070
Get the money ready.

355
00:26:48,070 --> 00:26:49,560
Or else,

356
00:26:50,530 --> 00:26:52,670
I'll go find her.

357
00:26:54,050 --> 00:26:57,660
Mind your own business. Tend to your own problems.

358
00:26:57,660 --> 00:27:00,100
Quit meddling in other people's issues.

359
00:27:05,450 --> 00:27:08,120
You did that because you thought I might get hurt.

360
00:27:08,820 --> 00:27:10,540
That's why...

361
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,630
you couldn't even give me this back then,

362
00:27:15,630 --> 00:27:18,160
and just walked away...

363
00:27:20,690 --> 00:27:22,980
After what Ms. Baek told me,

364
00:27:23,590 --> 00:27:26,080
I started worrying...

365
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:27,930
"What if he pushes me away again?"

366
00:27:27,930 --> 00:27:30,770
You have no idea how much I worried.

367
00:27:37,860 --> 00:27:40,260
That will never happen again.

368
00:27:42,140 --> 00:27:44,130
Now, I'll protect you.

369
00:27:45,130 --> 00:27:47,160
I will protect you.

370
00:27:50,230 --> 00:27:51,450
Forget it.

371
00:27:51,450 --> 00:27:53,160
I'll protect myself.

372
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:54,790
I'm Han Geum Ju.

373
00:27:54,790 --> 00:27:56,200
You saw me earlier, right?

374
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,370
I almost knocked out

375
00:27:57,370 --> 00:27:59,540
Seon Uk using my street fighter skills.

376
00:27:59,540 --> 00:28:02,720
That's who I am. So, don't worry.

377
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:05,920
Okay.

378
00:28:07,030 --> 00:28:09,390
And I'll protect you, too.

379
00:28:09,390 --> 00:28:10,830
Huh?

380
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:14,250
So,

381
00:28:15,290 --> 00:28:18,410
don't even think about leaving my side.

382
00:28:18,410 --> 00:28:20,390
No matter what happens.

383
00:28:21,180 --> 00:28:22,840
Got it?

384
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:30,250
That's reassuring.

385
00:28:33,940 --> 00:28:35,830
You bet.

386
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:54,720
[Bochun Chicken Soup]

387
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,230
What's this?

388
00:28:56,230 --> 00:28:57,730
I heard Seon Hwa is sick.

389
00:28:57,730 --> 00:29:01,450
She always says their chicken
soup gives her strength.

390
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,770
Instead of this,

391
00:29:03,770 --> 00:29:06,180
what if you gave it to her yourself?

392
00:29:06,990 --> 00:29:08,590
You know I can't.

393
00:29:08,590 --> 00:29:12,020
What if seeing me spikes her blood pressure?

394
00:29:12,020 --> 00:29:14,110
So, don't tell her this is from me.

395
00:29:14,110 --> 00:29:15,870
What are you doing?

396
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:24,180
Seon Hwa, I told you to rest at home.

397
00:29:24,180 --> 00:29:25,910
It's okay.

398
00:29:33,770 --> 00:29:36,960
Are you feeling okay?

399
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:40,250
What do you care?

400
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:41,430
Why did you bring that?

401
00:29:41,430 --> 00:29:43,210
Did you forget we're no longer friends?

402
00:29:43,210 --> 00:29:44,380
What do you mean "we"?

403
00:29:44,380 --> 00:29:46,840
You cut me off, but I didn't.

404
00:29:47,570 --> 00:29:48,610
What?

405
00:29:49,270 --> 00:29:51,720
Once time passes...

406
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:54,570
and Seon Uk meets a nice woman,

407
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:57,730
and once you feel better about it,

408
00:29:57,730 --> 00:30:00,370
we can be friends again...

409
00:30:01,050 --> 00:30:03,210
I'll wait until then.

410
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:09,700
Seon Uk is so worried about you.

411
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:12,070
He asked me to understand you

412
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:15,180
and go back to how we were before.

413
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:17,540
He hates that you might be lonely.

414
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:21,320
He cares about you a lot.

415
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:24,380
Because he's so thoughtful,

416
00:30:24,380 --> 00:30:27,730
that's probably why I wavered with Seon Uk.

417
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:33,390
I'm sorry I didn't tell you.

418
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:37,290
I just couldn't bring myself to say it.

419
00:30:37,290 --> 00:30:40,970
I thought I could take care
of it before you found out.

420
00:30:40,970 --> 00:30:43,390
So, I let go of my feelings,

421
00:30:43,390 --> 00:30:46,380
and I thought it was all over...

422
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:52,290
That jerk...

423
00:30:52,290 --> 00:30:54,030
ran away from home.

424
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:56,120
What?

425
00:31:07,270 --> 00:31:09,790
Hyeon Ju, come here.

426
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:15,250
Have a sip. This is quince tea.

427
00:31:15,250 --> 00:31:17,330
Smells amazing.

428
00:31:17,330 --> 00:31:18,970
Thank you.

429
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:24,690
You used to keep this cup on display
because it's so expensive.

430
00:31:24,690 --> 00:31:25,840
Right?

431
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,620
It's not like I can take it with me when I die.

432
00:31:27,620 --> 00:31:29,270
I don't know why I did that.

433
00:31:31,830 --> 00:31:33,920
Lying in the hospital bed,

434
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:36,100
thinking I might die,

435
00:31:36,100 --> 00:31:38,790
I started regretting all sorts of things.

436
00:31:39,840 --> 00:31:42,890
Like saving a stupid cup for later,

437
00:31:42,890 --> 00:31:45,940
or eating pork instead of beef
on my birthday last year.

438
00:31:45,940 --> 00:31:48,110
I had so many regrets.

439
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:49,880
Really?

440
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:54,800
But amidst everything, there was
one thing I didn't regret.

441
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,420
What was that?

442
00:31:57,610 --> 00:31:59,750
Marrying your father.

443
00:31:59,750 --> 00:32:01,500
Really?

444
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,250
You know, I was the eldest daughter

445
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:07,910
of a single mom with many younger siblings.

446
00:32:07,910 --> 00:32:10,450
Your dad was the eldest son of a rich family.

447
00:32:10,450 --> 00:32:13,350
He clung to me so hard until his opposing family

448
00:32:13,350 --> 00:32:15,340
finally came around.

449
00:32:16,010 --> 00:32:18,080
But I still refused.

450
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:20,340
I remember.

451
00:32:20,340 --> 00:32:23,220
But why did you act like that back then?

452
00:32:23,220 --> 00:32:26,650
Because I thought he was too good for me.

453
00:32:26,650 --> 00:32:29,950
I thought I'd ruin his life.

454
00:32:29,950 --> 00:32:33,780
So, how did you end up marrying him?

455
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:37,700
Weird, right?

456
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:41,900
The moment he said okay,
that he'd give up, and turned away,

457
00:32:43,290 --> 00:32:46,050
it felt like the sky was falling.

458
00:32:46,050 --> 00:32:47,430
So I mustered up courage,

459
00:32:47,430 --> 00:32:49,870
and turned him around.

460
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:55,310
Gosh, what if I'd just let him go then?

461
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:58,720
I would've regretted letting
a good man go my whole life.

462
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:01,400
I probably couldn't even die from the regret.

463
00:33:08,140 --> 00:33:10,670
So, don't make a decision you'll regret later.

464
00:33:10,670 --> 00:33:12,050
Huh?

465
00:33:13,010 --> 00:33:14,700
That jerk...

466
00:33:14,700 --> 00:33:16,640
ran away from home.

467
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:19,160
What?

468
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:22,190
He went to Geum Ju.

469
00:33:22,190 --> 00:33:25,560
Geum Ju told me. She was worried I'd worry.

470
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:27,820
She even knows where he is.

471
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:33,990
Could you please bring him back?

472
00:33:36,730 --> 00:33:37,850
What?

473
00:33:38,510 --> 00:33:39,740
Please.

474
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:42,950
You're the only one who can convince Seon Uk.

475
00:33:43,740 --> 00:33:45,340
Please...

476
00:33:46,110 --> 00:33:49,460
bring my brother back home. Please?

477
00:33:59,680 --> 00:34:02,230
You said you were swayed by Seon Uk.

478
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:06,180
Don't give up on that feeling.

479
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,440
I heard everything.

480
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:21,580
I visited Seon Hwa because I heard she was sick.

481
00:34:22,730 --> 00:34:24,340
Hyeon Ju.

482
00:34:25,460 --> 00:34:27,480
Seon Uk likes you...

483
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:30,540
and you like him, too. So what's there to hesitate?

484
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:33,130
Be brave.

485
00:34:33,130 --> 00:34:35,980
Don't end up with regrets.

486
00:34:43,940 --> 00:34:45,910
Honey.

487
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:49,170
Here, a gift.

488
00:34:49,170 --> 00:34:50,300
What's this?

489
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:52,180
I made it for you.

490
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:55,300
At the hospital, you said you wished you had

491
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:58,680
a small family portrait to carry around with you.

492
00:34:58,680 --> 00:35:00,440
Gosh, thank you.

493
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,040
It's so well made.

494
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:03,130
Do you like it?

495
00:35:03,130 --> 00:35:04,270
Yes.

496
00:35:05,090 --> 00:35:06,840
Nice!

497
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,810
Gosh, seriously...

498
00:35:08,810 --> 00:35:12,000
Wow, she brought out the fancy cups!

499
00:35:37,420 --> 00:35:39,770
Am I hallucinating now?

500
00:35:40,830 --> 00:35:42,560
Let's just forget.

501
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:43,920
Forget...

502
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:45,580
Where are you going?

503
00:35:52,460 --> 00:35:54,200
Let's talk.

504
00:35:59,810 --> 00:36:01,560
Han Geum Ju...

505
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:03,430
I told her not to say anything.

506
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:07,230
Why? So, you can hide forever?

507
00:36:07,890 --> 00:36:09,620
No.

508
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:11,990
I was actually on my way back to Bochun.

509
00:36:11,990 --> 00:36:14,880
After hearing about Ui Jun, I got to thinking.

510
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:18,500
If someone can endure that kind of nightmare,

511
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:21,320
then I shouldn't be whining.

512
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:27,200
I'll do better, so you don't get hurt

513
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:31,500
and so you can keep your friendship with my sister.

514
00:36:34,090 --> 00:36:36,540
I'll try my best for your sake.

515
00:36:39,550 --> 00:36:41,510
Though it'll be hard...

516
00:36:44,150 --> 00:36:46,560
I'm going to try to forget you.

517
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:53,180
Really?

518
00:36:56,120 --> 00:36:58,330
Then, I shouldn't have come.

519
00:36:58,330 --> 00:37:00,790
I came to say something,

520
00:37:00,790 --> 00:37:03,090
but I guess I don't need to say it anymore.

521
00:37:03,830 --> 00:37:05,300
Say something?

522
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:07,870
What is it?

523
00:37:10,250 --> 00:37:12,140
Let us date.

524
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:16,980
What?

525
00:37:16,980 --> 00:37:20,160
Gosh, but pretend you didn't hear it.

526
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:23,600
Since you decided to forget me, it's too bad.

527
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:26,280
Seon Hwa told me to give it a shot with you.

528
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:28,670
Wait, what are you saying...

529
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:31,630
My sister really said that?

530
00:37:31,630 --> 00:37:34,280
Yeah, but I'll tell her.

531
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,500
That you rejected me.

532
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:38,730
What? W-What are you talking about?

533
00:37:38,730 --> 00:37:41,220
What? Didn't you say you were going to forget me?

534
00:37:41,220 --> 00:37:42,860
That you were going to try?

535
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:44,140
I did?

536
00:37:44,140 --> 00:37:46,170
When? W-Wait...

537
00:37:46,170 --> 00:37:48,700
I take it back, spit, spit, spit!

538
00:37:50,940 --> 00:37:53,090
Hurry up and call your sister.

539
00:37:53,090 --> 00:37:56,630
I can't stand to see my precious friend worried.

540
00:37:56,630 --> 00:37:58,020
Okay.

541
00:38:02,290 --> 00:38:04,740
May I borrow your phone?

542
00:38:15,470 --> 00:38:18,000
Hello? Noona, it's me, Seon Uk.

543
00:38:18,740 --> 00:38:21,370
Hang on. I'm heading to Bochun right now.

544
00:38:23,980 --> 00:38:25,550
Thank you.

545
00:38:28,950 --> 00:38:30,600
Really.

546
00:38:43,020 --> 00:38:44,480
Wait.

547
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:54,030
[Mr. Seon Uk]

548
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:56,100
Mr. Seon Uk?

549
00:38:56,100 --> 00:38:58,180
We're officially dating now.

550
00:38:58,180 --> 00:38:59,880
Ms. Hyeon Ju.

551
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,000
No...

552
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:03,220
Should I say babe?

