resting place at some point.

596
00:42:10,220 --> 00:42:12,620
That's what led you to Bochun.

597
00:42:37,630 --> 00:42:39,340
Yes, Detective.

598
00:42:40,750 --> 00:42:42,110
Pardon?

599
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:49,680
[Bochun Funeral Home]

600
00:42:52,180 --> 00:42:55,360
He was found in the mountains
near your grandmother's grave.

601
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:58,070
His heart had already stopped.

602
00:42:58,070 --> 00:43:02,330
Cause of death is acute alcohol poisoning.

603
00:43:03,570 --> 00:43:05,940
Alcohol finally caught up to him.

604
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:19,190
Sir, may I speak with you?

605
00:43:19,190 --> 00:43:20,640
Yes.

606
00:43:32,150 --> 00:43:33,820
Here it is.

607
00:43:52,720 --> 00:43:54,260
Geum Ju.

608
00:43:55,380 --> 00:43:56,710
You can go now.

609
00:43:56,710 --> 00:43:59,860
No. I'll stay here, too.

610
00:43:59,860 --> 00:44:02,160
- Geum Ju.
- I said I'll stay.

611
00:44:03,780 --> 00:44:08,020
Are you really not going to call anyone?

612
00:44:10,150 --> 00:44:11,700
No.

613
00:44:11,700 --> 00:44:14,020
Please put it at the end there.

614
00:44:14,020 --> 00:44:15,750
Dad.

615
00:44:17,010 --> 00:44:18,650
Mom.

616
00:44:19,850 --> 00:44:21,890
How did you find us here?

617
00:44:21,890 --> 00:44:23,230
What do you think?

618
00:44:23,230 --> 00:44:24,720
I'm Kim Gwang Ok.

619
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:28,010
I know everything that goes down in Bochun.

620
00:44:28,010 --> 00:44:29,720
Why didn't you say anything?

621
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:31,200
You really should've.

622
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:33,560
I agree completely.

623
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:35,920
This is not something you should've kept quiet on.

624
00:44:35,920 --> 00:44:38,290
I told her not to say anything. I'm sorry.

625
00:44:38,290 --> 00:44:39,950
There, there.

626
00:44:39,950 --> 00:44:41,280
Please come in.

627
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:42,730
You're finally here.

628
00:44:42,730 --> 00:44:44,340
Over here, here.

629
00:44:45,220 --> 00:44:47,390
Put the food there.

630
00:44:47,390 --> 00:44:48,850
Put it here.

631
00:44:49,650 --> 00:44:51,220
Take this.

632
00:44:51,220 --> 00:44:53,510
Go on in.

633
00:44:53,510 --> 00:44:56,120
Bring them in. Put it over there.

634
00:44:56,120 --> 00:44:58,480
- Fill it from the end.
- Go all the way.

635
00:44:59,090 --> 00:45:00,330
Take this.

636
00:45:00,330 --> 00:45:01,780
Yes, yes...

637
00:45:07,350 --> 00:45:09,150
[Bochun Business Association]

638
00:45:09,150 --> 00:45:10,870
[Lake Bochun Pension]

639
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:41,630
Your knees will hurt from bowing.

640
00:45:41,630 --> 00:45:43,430
Keep them on, even if it's uncomfortable.

641
00:45:43,430 --> 00:45:44,550
Yes.

642
00:45:44,550 --> 00:45:47,480
You know from your grandmother's funeral.

643
00:45:49,230 --> 00:45:50,830
Thank you...

644
00:45:52,160 --> 00:45:53,270
Ui Jun.

645
00:45:53,270 --> 00:45:54,500
Yes.

646
00:45:54,500 --> 00:45:58,280
Don't keep standing there.
Take a few breaks when you can.

647
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:01,340
Yes, we laid down an electric blanket in there.

648
00:46:01,340 --> 00:46:02,650
We got some hot packs, too.

649
00:46:02,650 --> 00:46:04,210
It'll be cold when we head to the burial site.

650
00:46:04,210 --> 00:46:05,610
Take some with you.

651
00:46:05,610 --> 00:46:07,180
Thank you.

652
00:46:07,180 --> 00:46:09,580
You didn't need to do all this.

653
00:46:10,270 --> 00:46:12,170
You didn't even know my father...

654
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:16,900
Funerals are actually for the living, not the dead.

655
00:46:17,740 --> 00:46:19,300
Thank you.

656
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:37,600
I've never been to an alcohol-free funeral.

657
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:41,300
How dare you bring up booze?

658
00:46:41,300 --> 00:46:43,150
You know how Ui Jun's father died.

659
00:46:43,150 --> 00:46:44,690
Come on.

660
00:46:44,690 --> 00:46:46,900
Don't forget that we're pallbearers.

661
00:46:46,900 --> 00:46:48,410
At 8 a.m. on the third day.

662
00:46:48,410 --> 00:46:49,690
Yes.

663
00:46:50,690 --> 00:46:52,380
On the fourth day...

664
00:46:52,380 --> 00:46:55,170
at 8 a.m. Saved.

665
00:46:55,170 --> 00:46:56,420
No, the third day.

666
00:46:56,420 --> 00:46:58,190
Yes, four days.

667
00:46:58,190 --> 00:46:59,680
No, not four days. The third day.

668
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:01,880
First, second, third. On the third day.

669
00:47:01,880 --> 00:47:03,140
Not on the fourth day.

670
00:47:03,140 --> 00:47:04,230
- What?
- What?

671
00:47:04,230 --> 00:47:06,150
What are you talking about?

672
00:47:06,150 --> 00:47:07,220
I'm going crazy.

673
00:47:07,300 --> 00:47:11,700
Did I entrust the taekwondo studio
to this idiot and take off?

674
00:47:13,090 --> 00:47:16,460
I live with an idiot like him for a son.

675
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:21,100
Why did he torment such a kind
and smart son like Ui Jun?

676
00:47:21,100 --> 00:47:23,640
He thought it was revenge.

677
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:26,610
Against Ui Jun's mom, who abandoned him.

678
00:47:26,610 --> 00:47:28,800
What a horrible person...

679
00:47:28,800 --> 00:47:30,620
I agree completely.

680
00:47:30,620 --> 00:47:34,500
And yet he's throwing a funeral for such a father.

681
00:47:34,500 --> 00:47:36,560
I know, right? You won't find a better man

682
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:38,390
than Ui Jun these days.

683
00:47:38,390 --> 00:47:41,980
Yes, the more I get to know him,
the more I like him.

684
00:47:41,980 --> 00:47:43,300
Absolutely.

685
00:47:43,300 --> 00:47:46,240
Geum Ju, you really chose a good man.

686
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:48,570
They're a great match.

687
00:47:49,990 --> 00:47:51,310
You're blessed. Really blessed.

688
00:47:51,310 --> 00:47:53,350
Yes, thank you.

689
00:47:53,350 --> 00:47:55,170
That's right.

690
00:48:07,350 --> 00:48:09,260
Getting some fresh air?

691
00:48:09,260 --> 00:48:11,120
Huh? Yeah.

692
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:13,780
Everyone is saying I got lucky in love.

693
00:48:13,780 --> 00:48:15,630
You could've done nothing,
and no one would've blamed you.

694
00:48:15,630 --> 00:48:17,350
But you went as far as to hold a funeral.

695
00:48:17,350 --> 00:48:19,250
They're praising you nonstop,

696
00:48:19,300 --> 00:48:22,100
- saying you're so sweet and admirable.
- No.

697
00:48:24,410 --> 00:48:26,440
I'm a bad guy.

698
00:48:28,590 --> 00:48:32,220
I wanted to find him before
something tragic happened again.

699
00:48:32,220 --> 00:48:33,890
My father...

700
00:48:33,890 --> 00:48:37,190
This time, as a doctor,

701
00:48:37,190 --> 00:48:39,830
I wanted to hold on to him till the end.

702
00:48:43,620 --> 00:48:46,690
That's what I thought I felt.

703
00:48:49,970 --> 00:48:52,680
But when I heard he'd passed away,

704
00:48:53,830 --> 00:48:56,820
you know what my first thought was?

705
00:48:58,180 --> 00:49:00,740
That it's over now.

706
00:49:00,740 --> 00:49:02,430
It's finally over.

707
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:09,500
I felt relieved.

708
00:49:10,180 --> 00:49:12,030
I felt free.

709
00:49:13,810 --> 00:49:15,890
I'm a terrible person.

710
00:49:18,030 --> 00:49:19,730
I told you...

711
00:49:19,730 --> 00:49:21,890
not to torture yourself anymore.

712
00:49:21,890 --> 00:49:23,480
No.

713
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:28,150
As a doctor and as a son,

714
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:32,200
I'm not qualified.

715
00:49:37,960 --> 00:49:40,390
In the end, Ms. Baek...

716
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:45,650
ended up that way because of me.

717
00:49:45,650 --> 00:49:48,410
Not because of you. Because it's you.

718
00:49:50,820 --> 00:49:53,540
She did that because it's you.

719
00:49:58,430 --> 00:50:00,390
When my mom...

720
00:50:00,390 --> 00:50:03,740
desperately needed a liver transplant,

721
00:50:03,740 --> 00:50:05,970
she refused to let them cut me open.

722
00:50:05,970 --> 00:50:08,900
When I saw her say she'd rather die...

723
00:50:11,580 --> 00:50:14,320
I realized that's what being a mom means.

724
00:50:15,700 --> 00:50:19,800
Even if she dies, her baby must live.

725
00:50:20,490 --> 00:50:22,960
That's what a mom is.

726
00:50:26,710 --> 00:50:29,790
I'm sure Ms. Baek felt that way.

727
00:50:32,060 --> 00:50:35,180
She endured all that hellish time

728
00:50:35,180 --> 00:50:37,480
because you were there.

729
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:38,900
Because it was you.

730
00:50:38,900 --> 00:50:41,140
Ms. Baek endured, thanks to you.

